    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-28T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="612"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.7962/5–1646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-28T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 28, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>364. President Lleras apparently under misapprehension in indicating belief US
                    Govt participation in Soledad Airport (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>
                    346, May 16<note n="58" xml:id="d612fn58">Not printed; in this telegram
                        Ambassador Wiley indicated that this participation was an obstacle to the
                        Colombian desire to municipalize this airport (821.7962/5-1646).</note>)
                    should “revert” to <gloss target="#t_Col1">Col</gloss> Govt. This participation
                    represents <pb facs="0688" n="670" xml:id="pg_670"/> secret emergency
                    arrangement under Airport Development Program between US Govt and <gloss
                        target="#t_Pan1">Pan</gloss> American Airways without involvement <gloss
                        target="#t_Col1">Col</gloss> Govt. Case not parallel to that in Brazil where
                    inter-governmental agreements were made covering construction and operation of
                    airports which were always recognized as being and continuing to be property of
                        <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss> Govt. These agreements of course
                    provided for postwar return of property to <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss>
                    administration.</p>
                <p>If you believe it would be useful to do so, inform <gloss target="#t_Pres1"
                        >Pres</gloss> Lleras in secrecy along above lines, adding, if he inquires,
                    that US contribution to Soledad approximately $650,000.</p>
                <p>Keep Dept advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
